                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Bindra rsquo;s gun in Games museum
    Chandigarh: India rsquo;s only individual Olympic gold medal winner has had to part with his gun which brought him victory at the recent Beijing Olympic Games for placing it in the Olympic Museum in Switzerland.
    In a statement here, Bindra said that in response to a communication from the International Olympic Committee (IOC), he has donated his gold winning gun, jacket and shoes to be placed in the Olympic Museum adding to its permanent collection. 
    FIA move
    Paris: The Canadian Grand Prix was dropped from the 2009 calendar on Tuesday, leaving North America without a Formula One race for the first time in 43 years.
  Governing body FIA ratified its calendar for the coming season and omitted the Canadian GP, which was first held in 1967. 
    It rsquo;s the first time since 1987 that the Canadian GP won't be on the F1 schedule.
